ex√©cutable Rust est-il grand ?</a> fournit une excellente explication de la raison pour laquelle cela est important et une proc√©dure d√©taill√©e. En m√™me temps, <a href="https://github.com/johnthagen/min-sized-rust" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Minimizing Rust Binary Binary Size</a> est plus √† jour et a quelques recommandations suppl√©mentaires.</p><p>Rust est connu pour produire de gros binaires, mais vous pouvez demander au compilateur d&#x27;optimiser la taille de l&#x27;ex√©cutable final.</p><p>Cargo expose plusieurs options qui d√©terminent comment le compilateur g√©n√®re votre binaire. Les options &quot;recommand√©es&quot; pour les applications Tauri sont les suivantes :</p><div class="language-toml codeBlockContainer_Ckt0 theme-code-block" style="--prism-background-color:#282c34;--prism-color:#ffffff"><div class="codeBlockContent_biex"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-toml codeBlock_bY9V thin-scrollbar"><code class="codeBlockLines_e6Vv"><span class="token-line" style="color:#ffffff"><span class="token punctuation" style="color:#8dc891">[</span><span class="token table class-name" style="color:#FAC863">profile.release</span><span class="token punctuation" style="color:#8dc891">]</span><span class="token plain"></span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#ffffff"><span class="token plain"></span><span class="token key property" style="color:#5a9bcf">panic</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token punctuation" style="color:#8dc891">=</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token string" style="color:#8dc891">&quot;abort&quot;</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span class="token comment" style="color:#999999"># Strip expensive panic clean-up logic</span><span class="token plain"></span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#ffffff"><span class="token plain"></span><span class="token key property" style="color:#5a9bcf">codegen-units</span><span class="token plain"> </span><span